data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` construction no longer compiles. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex types ŌĆö column names are now uniquified/fully-qualified

Two changes hit you:

- **Shared property names** (`ShippingAddress.Street` / `BillingAddress.Street`) now get a numeric suffix to disambiguate. This generates a column-rename migration.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin column names explicitly so no rename migration is generated:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, preserve the old shorter name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on this interface now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging). Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ŌåÉ new parameter
    { /* logging ŌĆö use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

Add the same parameter to every other method you implement from the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
